Local Host HTTPS SETUP

1Ô∏è‚É£ Install Nginx on Windows 11
1Ô∏è‚É£ Download Nginx

Go to nginx.org ‚Üí Download

Download Mainline ‚Üí Windows zip

Extract to:

C:\nginx


You should have:

C:\nginx\nginx.exe
C:\nginx\conf\nginx.conf

2Ô∏è‚É£ Start Nginx

Open Command Prompt as Administrator:

cd C:\nginx
nginx


Test:

http://localhost


You should see ‚ÄúWelcome to nginx!‚Äù

To stop nginx:

nginx -s stop

PART 2Ô∏è‚É£ Install mkcert (Local SSL)
3Ô∏è‚É£ Install Chocolatey (if not installed)

Run PowerShell as Admin:

Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force
iwr https://community.chocolatey.org/install.ps1 -UseBasicParsing | iex

4Ô∏è‚É£ Install mkcert
choco install mkcert

5Ô∏è‚É£ Create Local Trusted Certificate
mkcert -install


Generate cert:

mkcert localhost 127.0.0.1 ::1


Files created:

localhost.pem
localhost-key.pem


Move them to:

C:\nginx\certs\

Move the mkcert files

Assuming mkcert generated files in your current folder:

move localhost.pem C:\nginx\certs\
move localhost-key.pem C:\nginx\certs\


PART 3Ô∏è‚É£ Configure Nginx HTTPS
6Ô∏è‚É£ Edit nginx.conf

Open:

C:\nginx\conf\nginx.conf

üîπ Replace or add this configuration:
worker_processes  1;

events {
    worker_connections  1024;
}

http {
    include       mime.types;
    default_type  application/octet-stream;

    sendfile        on;

    server {
        listen 80;
        server_name localhost;
        return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
    }

    server {
        listen 443 ssl;
        server_name localhost;

        ssl_certificate      C:/nginx/certs/localhost.pem;
        ssl_certificate_key  C:/nginx/certs/localhost-key.pem;

        root   C:/nginx/html;
        index  index.html index.php;

        location / {
            try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
        }
    }
}


‚ö†Ô∏è Important

Use forward slashes /

Use absolute paths

7Ô∏è‚É£ Restart Nginx
nginx -s stop
nginx

